dic literature, beginning from the four Vedas,  and the Upani\xc5\x92ads and Pur\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9aas, the glories of the Supreme Lord are celebrated. By performing Vedic rituals, discussing the Vedic philosophy and worshiping the Lord in devotional service, He is attained. Therefore the purpose of the Vedas is to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. The Vedas give us direction to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and the \nprocess of understanding. The ultimate goal is the Supreme Personality of \nGodhead.  confirms this in the following words: tat tu samanvay\xe2\x88\x92t. One can attain perfection by understanding Vedic literature, and one can understand his relationship with the Supreme Personality of Godhead by performing the different processes. Thus one can approach Him and at the end attain the supreme goal, who is no other than the Supreme Personality of Godhead. In this verse, however, the purpose of the Vedas, the understanding of the Vedas and the goal of Vedas are clearly defined.'

