Whoever knows Me as the Supreme Personality of Godhead, without doubting, is to be understood as the knower of everything, and he therefore engages himself in full devotional service, O son of Bharata
PURPORTThere are many philosophical speculations about the constitutional position of the living entities and the Supreme Absolute Truth. Now in this verse the Supreme Personality of Godhead clearly explains that anyone who knows Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as the Supreme Person is actually the knower of everything. \nThe imperfect knower goes on simply speculating about the Absolute Truth, but the perfect knower, without wasting his valuable time, engages directly in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness, the devotional service of the Supreme Lord. Throughout the whole of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, this fact is being stressed at every step. And still there are so many stubborn commentators on Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 who consider the Supreme Absolute Truth and the living entities to be one and the same.Vedic knowledge is called \xe2\x80\x9cruti learning by aural reception. One should \nactually receive the Vedic message from authorities like K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa and His representatives. Here K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa distinguishes everything very nicely, and one should hear from this source. Simply to hear like the hogs is not sufficient; one must be able to understand from the authorities. It is not that one should simply speculate academically. One should submissively hear from Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 that these living entities are always subordinate to the Supreme \nPersonality of Godhead. Anyone who is able to understand this, according to '
the Supreme Personality of Godhead, \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, knows the purpose of the Vedas; no one else knows the purpose of the Vedas.The word bhajate is very significant. In many places the word bhajate is expressed in relationship with the service of the Supreme Lord. If a person is engaged in full K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness in devotional service of the Lord, it is to be understood that he has understood all the Vedic knowledge. In the Vai\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aava parampar\xe2\x88\x92 it is said that if one is engaged in the devotional service of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa, then there is no need for a spiritual process to understand the \nSupreme Absolute Truth. He has already come to the post because he is engaged in the devotional service of the Lord. He has ended all preliminary processes of understanding; similarly, if anyone, after speculating for hundreds of thousands of lives, does not come to the point that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead and that one has to surrender there, all his speculation for so many years and lives is a useless waste of time.
